### NILM Energy Prediction API - Endpoint Tests

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

### 1. Health Check - Check service status
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### 2. Detailed Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 3. Run complete prediction pipeline
# Reads data, preprocesses, runs inference and saves to cache
GET {{baseUrl}}/run-pipeline

### 4. Get cached predictions
# Returns the latest saved predictions
GET {{baseUrl}}/cached-predictions

### 5. Get aggregated statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/statistics

### 6. Custom data prediction (POST)
# Send data sequences to get predictions
POST {{baseUrl}}/predict
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "data": [
        [[0.5, 0.3, 0.7, 0.2, 0.8, 0.1, 0.9]],
        [[0.6, 0.4, 0.6, 0.3, 0.7, 0.2, 0.8]]
    ],
    "format": "array"
}

### 7. Test non-existent endpoint (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/nonexistent